{
  "text": "To examine the main effect of age, we then compared whole night mean data between age groups. A significant effect of age was found in slow wave distance (F (2,26) = 5.22, p = 0.01). Post-hoc tests revealed a difference between 2-to 4.9-year-old children and 9-to 16.9-year-olds ( Figure 4A ), confirming earlier results [CITATION_1] .",
